---
// /brands/milnor-commercial-laundry-repair/, Cluster 10 Laundry
// Pellerin Milnor Corp, Kenner LA (Louisiana, NOT Los Angeles). Independent family since 1947.
// Industrial tier above commercial. CBW tunnel washer flagship. Legacy 301: /milnor-commercial-dryer-repair/ (32 imp).
// URL scope extends washer + extractor + dryer per H2 structure.
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "Milnor Commercial Laundry Repair Los Angeles — Same Day";
const description = "Pellerin Milnor CBW tunnel, washer-extractor, MWF/MWR dryer repair Southern California. Hospital/hotel/studio. $120. (424) 325-0520.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/milnor-commercial-laundry-repair/";

const faqs = [
  { q: "Who owns Milnor?", a: "Pellerin Milnor Corporation is independent family-owned, headquartered in Kenner, Louisiana, not Los Angeles; the abbreviation 'LA' in the brand's address refers to the state of Louisiana. The company has operated under continuous Pellerin family ownership since 1947 and has not been folded into Ali Group, ITW Food Equipment, Middleby, Welbilt, Alliance Laundry Systems, or any of the conglomerate-ownership structures that consolidate most other industrial laundry brands. Independent family ownership matters operationally: Milnor's R&D is internally directed at industrial-tier applications, tunnel washing systems, high-capacity extractors, open-pocket dryers, rather than being shaped by conglomerate-integration priorities. For LA industrial laundry processors and hospital central laundries running Milnor, that independence translates to stable engineering direction and predictable long-run parts-chain support." },
  { q: "What's a CBW tunnel washer?", a: "CBW stands for Continuous Batch Washer, Milnor's flagship industrial washing system. Instead of loading, washing, and unloading one batch at a time like a conventional washer-extractor, a CBW is a long multi-module tunnel through which fabric moves continuously: one module pre-washes, the next washes with chemistry, later modules rinse, and the final module transfers to an extractor. Capacity is measured in pounds per hour rather than pounds per load, large CBW installations process 2,000–5,000+ pounds per hour. LA install base: regional linen-rental processing plants (Alsco, Cintas central facilities), large hospital central laundries, and large hotel central processing. CBW service is a different scope than conventional washer-extractor repair, mechanical components span dozens of interconnected modules, and diagnostic work requires understanding module-to-module transfer timing. We maintain the specialty skill set for CBW service across LA industrial operators." },
  { q: "Milnor vs Alliance UniMac, which industrial tier do I need?", a: "Both are industrial tier, but for different operational scales. UniMac (Alliance's heavy-duty industrial tier) is specified for hotel central laundry, mid-to-large hospital linen processing, and mid-scale industrial laundry, typically with batch washers + single-pocket dryers in the 75–120 pound range. Milnor sits at an industrial-plus tier, specified for regional linen processors, very large hospital central laundries, large hotel chain central processing, film/TV studio wardrobe processing, and operations where CBW tunnel washers or very large extractors (capacity past 250 pounds per batch) are the right scale. If your operation runs single-pocket dryers at 50–120 pound capacity, UniMac or Speed Queen Commercial is usually correct. If you run tunnel washers or 250+ pound extractors, you're in Milnor territory. The two overlap at the upper UniMac / lower Milnor boundary, and many large LA operations run mixed Alliance + Milnor rooms." },
  { q: "Do you service Milnor at LA hospitals and film studios?", a: "Yes, LA hospital central laundry and film + TV studio wardrobe laundry are two of the densest Milnor verticals in the region. Cedars-Sinai central laundry runs Milnor at industrial tier for the full hospital-system linen processing load; Kaiser Permanente's regional processing runs Milnor at several campuses; Keck Medical Center, UCLA Health, and Children's Hospital Los Angeles round out the hospital-side Milnor install base. Film and television wardrobe laundry at the major studios, Warner Bros, Universal, Paramount, Fox/Disney, runs Milnor for the high-volume costume + set-linen processing that's distinctive to production work. Regional linen-rental processors (Alsco LA, Cintas West Coast regional plants, Unifirst, Aramark hospital-linen) also run Milnor at industrial tier. These calls prioritize same-day because downtime on an industrial Milnor cascades into missed delivery windows across dozens of downstream customers." },
  { q: "CBW tunnel module-to-module transfer is failing, diagnostic?", a: "Module-to-module transfer failure on a CBW tunnel washer is a specialty diagnostic. The symptom is typically: fabric stops advancing at a specific module boundary, batch count falls behind, or the tunnel slows below production rate. Possible causes include hydraulic ram failure at the transfer cylinder, pneumatic door solenoid failure at the module seal, PLC communication loss between module controllers, fabric packing (too-dense load preventing pass-through), or chemistry imbalance causing fabric to bond and jam. Our diagnostic starts at the failure-module location: physically verify the transfer mechanism actuation, check PLC fault history at the module and the master controller, inspect the chemistry dose records for the hour before failure, and manually cycle the transfer with the tunnel in maintenance mode. Most tunnel-transfer calls resolve at the hydraulic or pneumatic actuation side; PLC communication issues are the second-most common; fabric-packing issues trace back to load-in protocol at the operator side." },
  { q: "What does Milnor repair cost in LA?", a: "$120 flat commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. Industrial-tier Milnor service typically runs higher than Alliance commercial/industrial because the equipment is larger and parts costs are higher. Typical Milnor service ranges: washer-extractor door gasket $280–$480, pressure switch / sensor $240–$400, water-inlet valve $260–$440, drive belt (large-capacity) $280–$480, chemistry pump integration service $300–$500, hydraulic actuator service (CBW or extractor) $420–$780, drum-bearing rebuild (large-capacity) $900–$1,600, main motor service $620–$1,100, PLC module replacement $1,200–$2,400, CBW module-transfer diagnostic + repair $680–$1,800 depending on root cause, variable-frequency drive replacement $1,400–$2,600. Most Milnor calls land $450–$1,200 parts-and-labor. CBW tunnel work and bearing rebuilds run at the higher end. See our <a href=\"/price-list/commercial-dryer-repair-cost/\">commercial dryer repair cost guide</a>." }
];

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@graph": [
    { "@type": "LocalBusiness", "@id": canonical + "#business", "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair", "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/logo.png", "url": "https://samedayappliance.repair/", "telephone": MAIN_PHONE, "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ] },
    { "@type": "Service", "serviceType": "Milnor Industrial Laundry Repair", "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" }, "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ], "description": "Pellerin Milnor industrial laundry repair across Los Angeles, CBW tunnel washers, 36026V7J and 42026V7J washer-extractors, MWF/MWR open-pocket dryers, 76058 extractor. Independent family-owned since 1947, Kenner Louisiana. LA hospital central laundry, hotel central, film + TV studio wardrobe, regional linen-rental processor specialists." },
    { "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({ "@type": "Question", "name": f.q, "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a.replace(/<[^>]+>/g, '') } })) },
    { "@type": "BreadcrumbList", "itemListElement": [ { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" }, { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" }, { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Milnor Industrial Laundry Repair", "item": canonical } ] }
  ]
};
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />
  <div class="call-banner"><div class="wrap"><span>Milnor down? Same-day industrial service:</span><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="phone-lg">{MAIN_PHONE}</a></div></div>
  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap"><div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › Milnor</div><h1>Milnor Industrial Laundry Repair</h1><p class="lede">Pellerin Milnor CBW tunnel washers, 36026V7J and 42026V7J washer-extractors, MWF/MWR open-pocket dryers, and 76058 extractors, our techs service the full Milnor industrial lineup across LA, Orange County, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside. Independent family-owned since 1947, Kenner Louisiana (the company's 'LA' is the state, not Los Angeles). LA hospital central laundry, hotel central processing, film + TV studio wardrobe, and regional linen-rental processor specialists; $120 diagnostic waived with repair.</p><div class="hero-cta"><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a><a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a></div><ul class="hero-facts"><li><b>Pellerin family since 1947</b>, Kenner Louisiana; independent; NOT Alliance / Ali / ITW / conglomerate</li><li><b>CBW tunnel washer specialist</b>, industrial continuous-batch system, 2,000–5,000+ lb/hr</li><li><b>LA hospital + studio vertical</b>, Cedars-Sinai, Kaiser, Warner Bros, Universal, Fox</li><li><b>Regional linen-rental</b>, Alsco, Cintas, Aramark hospital-linen processing plants</li></ul></div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />
  <section class="trust-bar"><div class="wrap"><span>Licensed BHGS #A49573 · Insured</span><span>Same-day · 5 SoCal counties</span><span>$120 commercial diagnostic · waived with repair</span></div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Pellerin Milnor, Kenner Louisiana, independent since 1947</h2>
    <p>Pellerin Milnor Corporation has manufactured industrial laundry equipment from Kenner, Louisiana since 1947, independent family-owned continuously for 78 years. One address note worth flagging: Milnor's Kenner LA location uses 'LA' as the Louisiana state abbreviation, not Los Angeles; operators sometimes assume there's a local Milnor facility in Southern California, but there isn't. Parts and factory engineering support route out of Kenner through Milnor's national distributor channel; LA-local service depends on distributor-carried inventory for common items and Kenner-routed orders for specialty components.</p>
    <p>Independence is the defining operational signature. Where most industrial equipment brands in the US have been consolidated under Ali Group, ITW Food Equipment Group, Middleby, Welbilt, or, for laundry specifically, Alliance Laundry Systems, Milnor has remained a privately-held Pellerin family company. That shapes the engineering roadmap: Milnor specializes in industrial-tier applications, tunnel washing systems (CBW), high-capacity extractors, and open-pocket dryers for operations processing thousands of pounds per hour. The Milnor product line isn't Alliance's lineup with different badging; it's a different product philosophy targeted at genuinely industrial laundry scale.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Milnor equipment we service</h2>
    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card"><h3>CBW, Continuous Batch Washer (tunnel)</h3><p>Milnor's flagship industrial washing system. Multi-module tunnel through which fabric moves continuously, pre-wash, main-wash with chemistry, rinse, transfer to extractor. 2,000–5,000+ lb/hr throughput. LA install: regional linen processors, large hospital central laundries, large hotel central processing. Service spans hydraulic actuators, pneumatic module seals, PLC module-to-module communication, chemistry dosing integration.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>36026V7J / 42026V7J washer-extractor</h3><p>Open-pocket washer-extractor models. Capacity series with V7J variable-speed extraction. Hospital + hotel central laundry workhorse. Service: inverter drive (extraction VFD), door gasket (large-diameter), water-inlet valves (multiple), drum-bearing assembly, chemistry-pump integration.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>MWF / MWR open-pocket dryer</h3><p>Milnor's single-pocket dryers for industrial-capacity drying, larger than UniMac UT075N, typically 100–300 lb capacity. Gas or steam-heated variants. Service: burner assembly, gas train, steam-coil integration (steam variants), air-flow pressure switch, exhaust thermistor, drum-bearing service.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>76058 extractor</h3><p>Stand-alone hydro-extractor for industrial operations using separate wash and extract steps. High G-force extraction substantially reduces downstream dryer time. Service focus: bearing assembly (very high G-force puts extreme load on bearings), pneumatic door seal, safety interlocks (critical at industrial extraction speeds), VFD integration.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>PLC + chemistry + integration controls</h3><p>Industrial Milnor installations integrate with chemistry-dispensing systems (Ecolab, Hydro Systems, comparable) and central laundry management systems. PLC module replacement, sensor drift diagnosis, and communication-fault work are routine service items at industrial scale. Our techs maintain the Milnor PLC fault-code library for these calls.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Steam and thermal integration</h3><p>Industrial Milnor at hospital and hotel central laundry typically integrates with facility steam systems, steam-heated washers, steam coils in dryers. Steam-side service (valves, traps, pressure regulation) overlaps with facility engineering but Milnor-specific integration points (condensate return at equipment, steam-coil sensors) sit in our scope.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>LA hospital + studio + linen-rental, Milnor install concentration</h2>
    <p>Milnor's LA install base concentrates at the industrial scale, operations where UniMac or Speed Queen Commercial capacity would be insufficient. Three dominant verticals:</p>
    <p><b>Hospital central laundry.</b> Cedars-Sinai central laundry runs Milnor at industrial tier for the full hospital-system linen load. Kaiser Permanente's regional processing runs Milnor at several campuses; Keck Medical Center, UCLA Health, and Children's Hospital Los Angeles round out the hospital-side Milnor base. Hospital linen processing has specific operational requirements, bloodborne-pathogen handling, medical-grade chemistry dosing, traceability per health-department requirements, that shape Milnor installation spec.</p>
    <p><b>Film and television studio wardrobe.</b> Warner Bros, Universal, Paramount, and Fox/Disney studios all run Milnor for high-volume costume, set linen, and wardrobe processing. Studio laundry is distinctive: high-variety wash loads (different fabrics each day as production schedules change), same-day-turnaround requirements when a production is filming, and fabric-handling specifications for costume pieces that can't tolerate standard industrial processing.</p>
    <p><b>Regional linen-rental processors.</b> Alsco LA regional plant, Cintas West Coast facilities, Aramark hospital-linen processing, and Unifirst uniform-rental operations all run Milnor CBW tunnels + industrial dryers at scale. These plants process thousands of pounds per hour through continuous shift operations, Milnor downtime cascades into missed delivery windows across dozens of downstream customer accounts.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Alliance vs Milnor, the operational distinction</h2>
    <p>Operators moving from Alliance Speed Queen or UniMac installations into Milnor territory sometimes assume the service approach is the same. It isn't, industrial Milnor is a different scope. The equipment is physically larger (tunnel washers span 40+ feet; extractors at 250+ pound capacity have mass that makes residential tools irrelevant). Diagnostic work uses PLC fault codes rather than control-panel LED readouts. Parts lead time is longer because components are manufacturer-specific and ship from Kenner. And labor time per repair is longer because access and work area are industrial-scale.</p>
    <p>That said, the fundamental mechanical domains are recognizable: bearings, motors, drive belts, door gaskets, water-inlet valves, pressure switches. The troubleshooting logic extends from commercial to industrial with scale adjustments. For LA operators running mixed Alliance (Speed Queen / UniMac) + Milnor installations, common at hotel central laundries and regional processors, our coverage spans both with the scope-appropriate diagnostic approach for each. When a call comes in, we ask what equipment is down before dispatching so we send the right truck-load of parts.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>What Milnor repair costs in LA</h2>
    <p>$120 flat commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. Industrial-tier pricing runs higher than Alliance commercial/industrial because the equipment is larger and parts costs are higher.</p>
    <table class="price-table"><thead><tr><th>Repair</th><th>Typical range (parts + labor)</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Pressure switch / sensor</td><td>$240–$400</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Water-inlet valve</td><td>$260–$440</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Washer-extractor door gasket</td><td>$280–$480</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Drive belt (large-capacity)</td><td>$280–$480</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Chemistry pump integration service</td><td>$300–$500</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Hydraulic actuator service (CBW or extractor)</td><td>$420–$780</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Main motor service</td><td>$620–$1,100</td></tr>
      <tr><td>CBW module-transfer repair</td><td>$680–$1,800</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Drum-bearing rebuild (large-capacity)</td><td>$900–$1,600</td></tr>
      <tr><td>PLC module replacement</td><td>$1,200–$2,400</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Variable-frequency drive replacement</td><td>$1,400–$2,600</td></tr>
    </tbody></table>
    <p class="small">Most Milnor calls land $450–$1,200 parts-and-labor. CBW tunnel work and bearing rebuilds run at the higher end. See our <a href="/price-list/commercial-dryer-repair-cost/">commercial dryer repair cost guide</a>.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Related Milnor and industrial laundry pages</h2>
    <ul class="related-links">
      <li><a href="/brands/unimac-commercial-laundry-repair/">UniMac commercial laundry repair Los Angeles</a>, Alliance heavy-duty industrial sibling (UT075N + UT-series)</li>
      <li><a href="/brands/speed-queen-commercial-laundry-repair/">Speed Queen Commercial laundry repair Los Angeles</a>, Alliance flagship commercial tier</li>
      <li><a href="/brands/adc-commercial-dryer-repair/">ADC American Dryer Corp repair Los Angeles</a>, industrial dryer specialist (competing tier)</li>
      <li><a href="/commercial/laundry-repair/">All commercial laundry repair in Los Angeles →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/commercial/washer-repair/">Commercial washer repair</a> · <a href="/commercial/">Commercial dryer repair</a></li>
      <li><a href="/price-list/commercial-dryer-repair-cost/">Commercial dryer repair cost</a></li>
      <li><a href="/downtown-la/">Downtown LA service area</a> · <a href="/burbank/">Burbank service area</a> · <a href="/culver-city/">Culver City service area</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow"><h2>Milnor repair, frequently asked</h2>{faqs.map(f => <details class="faq"><summary>{f.q}</summary><p set:html={f.a}></p></details>)}</div></section>

  <section id="book" class="cta-bottom"><div class="wrap"><h2>Milnor down? Call the branch nearest your processing facility.</h2><p>Same-day in LA, Orange County, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside. $120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair.</p></div></section>
  <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="float-call" aria-label="Call now">☎ Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a>
</Layout>

